WorkItem.Description: OK in feral dps , I have 384 Maxtrix, 378 Hunger, according to RAWR with t13 4pc my dps is around 35862. Now RAWR says that the upgrades to 378 Hungerer are a slew of 346 tia/s grace's and most of all If i use Fluid death (359) with the matrix my dps goes from 35862 to 38597? Thats 3000 dps on a 359 trinket that supposedly the only other trinkets over it are Both Wrath of Unchaning. How can Fluid Death be 3rd BIS , please tell me this is a coding error as I have a 4pc t13 and cant try to test this without being in a raid , I would like to know if this is a coding error, as all New Dragon soul trinkets are placed below Fluid Death other than the Wraths of Unchaining?
WorkItem.Summary: [Cat] Possible trinket prioritization error in rawr

Comments.Message: if one edits the item in question and hard codes its agility at 380 it is placed more reasonably. So seemingly rawr overvalues agility on proc
Yeah, note my ticket about wacky interactions and a 14000 point upgrade using Fluid Death on my rogue.  I just removed it from my list of available items and went on about my business.

There's strange things going on with trinkets...

This is for my protection paladin:
http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/6/73262601.jpg/

Notice how Spidersilk Spindle has an insane high score compared to the (much better) trinket Fire of the Deep.
